{"description": "The <tt>auditd</tt> service can be configured to\nsynchronously write audit event data to disk. Add or correct the following\nline in <tt>/etc/audit/auditd.conf</tt> to ensure that audit event data is\nfully synchronized with the log files on the disk:\n<pre>flush = <sub idref=\"var_auditd_flush\" /></pre>", "rationale": "Audit data should be synchronously written to disk to ensure\nlog integrity. These parameters assure that all audit event data is fully\nsynchronized with the log files on the disk.", "severity": "medium", "references": {"cis-csc": ["1", "12", "13", "14", "15", "16", "2", "3", "5", "6", "7", "8", "9"], "cobit5": ["APO10.01", "APO10.03", "APO10.04", "APO10.05", "APO11.04", "BAI03.05", "DSS01.03", "DSS03.05", "DSS05.02", "DSS05.04", "DSS05.05", "DSS05.07", "MEA01.01", "MEA01.02", "MEA01.03", "MEA01.04", "MEA01.05", "MEA02.01"], "cui": ["3.3.1"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(1)(ii)(D)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "164.308(a)(5)(ii)(C)", "164.312(a)(2)(i)", "164.312(b)", "164.312(d)", "164.312(e)"], "isa-62443-2009": ["4.3.2.6.7", "4.3.3.3.9", "4.3.3.5.8", "4.3.4.4.7", "4.4.2.1", "4.4.2.2", "4.4.2.4"], "isa-62443-2013": ["SR 2.10", "SR 2.11", "SR 2.12", "SR 2.8", "SR 2.9", "SR 6.1", "SR 6.2"], "iso27001-2013": ["A.12.4.1", "A.12.4.2", "A.12.4.3", "A.12.4.4", "A.12.7.1", "A.14.2.7", "A.15.2.1", "A.15.2.2"], "nerc-cip": ["CIP-004-6 R2.2.3", "CIP-004-6 R3.3", "CIP-007-3 R5.2", "CIP-007-3 R5.3.1", "CIP-007-3 R5.3.2", "CIP-007-3 R5.3.3", "CIP-007-3 R6.5"], "nist": ["AU-11", "CM-6(a)"], "nist-csf": ["DE.CM-1", "DE.CM-3", "DE.CM-7", "ID.SC-4", "PR.PT-1"], "ospp": ["FAU_GEN.1"], "srg": ["SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"], "ism": ["0582"]}, "control_references": {"ism": ["0582"]}, "components": ["audit"], "identifiers": {"cce": "CCE-83685-8"}, "ocil_clause": "auditd is not configured to synchronously write audit event data to disk", "ocil": "Inspect <tt>/etc/audit/auditd.conf</tt> and locate the following line to\ndetermine if the system is configured to synchr